<br>
What I see people would like is a skill comparable (not like) to mana burn, which has the same WOW-factor as the big BOOM from manaburn.<br>
<br>
What manaburn does is taking all the wizards mana and converts it into a big hurt, where each mana point is approximately equal to 2 dmg + focus effects + criticals. The result is that the wizard can make big things dead fast, BUT also leaves the wizard vulnable because he has used all his mana and if what he hit didn't die, he is very high on the hate list and therefore very likely to get summoned and killed. It is exactly this that balances the benefit and risk.<br>
<br>
A magician is not designed to do as much DD as a wizard, but it does not mean that the magician isn't a damage dealer.<br>
<br>
I suggest a different approach.<br>
<br>
Using the elemental forms as a base, the magician get a skill that reclaims the pet and based on the pets hitpoint, scaled in some way, can use this to do some damage.<br>
<br>
It could be:<br>
<br>
Elemental Form: Fire: Big fire based nuke which does pet hp * 2 + focus + critical<br>
Elemental Form: Water: Big cold based nuke which does pet hp * 2 + focus + critical<br>
Elemental Form: Air: Big magic based nuke which does pet hp * 2 + focus + critical<br>
Elemental Form: earth: The magician in earth form can do a massive mele damage over a very short period or one single blow for max damage and the magician has to be in mele range. The damage is based on the pets hp.<br>
<br>
What you get is the wow-effect with a very visible damage AND you get the risk like the manaburn, where you are put high on the hate list. You also get the added risk from loosing the pet and you would have to resummon one.<br>
<br>
nmee, lv 54 magician on Xev<br>
